defs.docs: Runtime support for the `wasm-bindgen` tool

defs.name: prelude
defs.docs: A module which is typically glob imported from:

defs.name: convert
defs.docs:
This is mostly an internal module, no stability guarantees are provided. Use
 at your own risk.

defs.name: IntoWasmAbi
defs.docs:
A trait for anything that can be converted into a type that can cross the
 wasm ABI directly, eg `u32` or `f64`.

defs.name: Abi
defs.docs:
The wasm ABI type that this converts into when crossing the ABI
 boundary.

defs.name: into_abi
defs.docs:
Convert `self` into `Self::Abi` so that it can be sent across the wasm
 ABI boundary.

defs.name: FromWasmAbi
defs.docs:
A trait for anything that can be recovered by-value from the wasm ABI
 boundary, eg a Rust `u8` can be recovered from the wasm ABI `u32` type.

defs.name: Abi
defs.docs:
The wasm ABI type that this converts from when coming back out from the
 ABI boundary.

defs.name: from_abi
defs.docs: Recover a `Self` from `Self::Abi`.

defs.name: RefFromWasmAbi
defs.docs:
A trait for anything that can be recovered as some sort of shared reference
 from the wasm ABI boundary.

defs.name: Abi
defs.docs: The wasm ABI type references to `Self` are recovered from.

defs.name: Anchor
defs.docs:
The type that holds the reference to `Self` for the duration of the
 invocation of the function that has an `&Self` parameter. This is
 required to ensure that the lifetimes don't persist beyond one function
 call, and so that they remain anonymous.

defs.name: ref_from_abi
defs.docs: Recover a `Self::Anchor` from `Self::Abi`.

defs.name: RefMutFromWasmAbi
defs.docs: Dual of the `RefFromWasmAbi` trait, except for mutable references.

defs.name: Abi
defs.docs: Same as `RefFromWasmAbi::Abi`

defs.name: Anchor
defs.docs: Same as `RefFromWasmAbi::Anchor`

defs.name: ref_mut_from_abi
defs.docs: Same as `RefFromWasmAbi::ref_from_abi`

defs.name: OptionIntoWasmAbi
defs.docs: Indicates that this type can be passed to JS as `Option<Self>`.

defs.name: none
defs.docs:
Returns an ABI instance indicating "none", which JS will interpret as
 the `None` branch of this option.

defs.name: OptionFromWasmAbi
defs.docs: Indicates that this type can be received from JS as `Option<Self>`.

defs.name: is_none
defs.docs:
Tests whether the argument is a "none" instance. If so it will be
 deserialized as `None`, and otherwise it will be passed to
 `FromWasmAbi`.

defs.name: WasmAbi
defs.docs:
An unsafe trait which represents types that are ABI-safe to pass via wasm
 arguments.

defs.name: ReturnWasmAbi
defs.docs:
A trait representing how to interepret the return value of a function for
 the wasm ABI.

defs.name: Abi
defs.docs: Same as `IntoWasmAbi::Abi`

defs.name: return_abi
defs.docs:
Same as `IntoWasmAbi::into_abi`, except that it may throw and never
 return in the case of `Err`.

defs.name: describe
defs.docs:
This is an internal module, no stability guarantees are provided. Use at
 your own risk.

defs.name: JsCast
defs.docs: A trait for checked and unchecked casting between JS types.

defs.name: is_instance_of
defs.docs: Test whether this JS value is an instance of the type `T`.

defs.name: dyn_into
defs.docs:
Performs a dynamic cast (checked at runtime) of this value into the
 target type `T`.

defs.name: dyn_ref
defs.docs:
Performs a dynamic cast (checked at runtime) of this value into the
 target type `T`.

defs.name: unchecked_into
defs.docs: Performs a zero-cost unchecked cast into the specified type.

defs.name: unchecked_ref
defs.docs:
Performs a zero-cost unchecked cast into a reference to the specified
 type.

defs.name: instanceof
defs.docs:
Performs a dynamic `instanceof` check to see whether the `JsValue`
 provided is an instance of this type.

defs.name: unchecked_from_js
defs.docs:
Performs a zero-cost unchecked conversion from a `JsValue` into an
 instance of `Self`

defs.name: unchecked_from_js_ref
defs.docs:
Performs a zero-cost unchecked conversion from a `&JsValue` into an
 instance of `&Self`.

defs.name: forget

 entire program.
